BelongText1: I moved here at around 13-14, so I didn't really have a say or a choice. I came in as a book worm and like an intellectual. There is nothing but hicks and rednecks around here, who are very mechanically oriented and smart in that sense, but nobody here reads books or I think even knows how to pick up a book and read from it. I have slowly but surely adapted into this blue collar drunkard mindset, but I can't help but feel like there is somewhere else calling my name where I would truly feel at home and not feel like I have to just play along with what everyone around me is saying thinking doing and believing just so that I can be a 'Pennsylvanian.' I like the place well enough I guess, but I have never once really felt like I was at home in the deepest parts of my heart and soul in my time living here, and I am now 25 years of age. I hope to one day move somewhere far, far, far away, and find my true home, which I do still believe is in the United States of America as it's a good place
